docs.abstract: A proposed deepwater port could recast the former Soviet republic’s image. But not without the backing of Bidzina Ivanishvili, a billionaire and power broker.
docs.snippet: A proposed deepwater port could recast the former Soviet republic’s image. But not without the backing of Bidzina Ivanishvili, a billionaire and power broker.
docs.lead_paragraph: TBILISI, Georgia — The republic of Georgia’s richest citizen, Bidzina Ivanishvili, is a born builder. He owns what is easily Tbilisi’s most eye-catching private structure, a futuristic, $50 million steel-and-glass castle, nicknamed “the glassle,” on a hill near the city’s historic neighborhood. It is a 107,000-square-foot personal office, complete with a helipad, a collection of modern art and a shark tank.

headline.main: High in His ‘Glassle,’ Georgia’s Richest Man Looms Over Country’s Top Project
headline.print_headline: A Country’s Image Hangs in the Balance
